    "body": "It might throw an error saving as ShpTD - my version of SHP builder scews the shptd format up, so that openRA throws an error. Save instead as ShpTS and convert with XCC Utilities to .png->ShpTD. Thats what I allways do. \r\nI don't know a way to convert to .R8 either.. ^^\r\n\r\nI would perfer if the unit stances visibility could be toggled on/off, like the health bars. Maybe you can simply alter the selection brackets to have a different color on a different stance? Theat would not be as clear as text, but if you knew what the colors mean, that would be a minimal UI solution."
