    "created_at": "2017-05-26T17:50:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-05-26T18:00:31Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We are already planning to finish implementing the unit stance logic in the immediate future to go along with the building TargetableLocations change, so IMO the most reasonable way forward here is to go all the way and implement the stance selection UI from the later games.  This then naturally wraps up the planned work and avoids all the issues that come with per-unit decorations.\r\n\r\ne.g. from C&C3:\r\n<img width=\"550\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-05-26 at 18 37 56\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/167819/26506088/2c55ab78-4243-11e7-8ca9-68491b64759c.png\">\r\n\r\nThe four right-most buttons map to HoldFire / ReturnFire / Defend / AttackAnything, and are highlighted based on the stances of the selected units.\r\n\r\nThis is another very-long planned feature (e.g. #3789 and linked tickets) that has never gone anywhere mainly because people wanted to scope-creep it into a dynamic order palette.  I'm suggesting that we officially give up on that idea, and instead duplicate the fixed C&C3 bar with buttons for our three primary order generators (force-move, attack-move, guard) and the four stances.\r\n\r\nThis is something i'm prepared to implement myself once the other high-priority half-finished features for the next release are done."
  },
